verbose_text: The hypothesis that IGF-1 / AKT attenuation contributes to cancer cachexia is supported by the presently observed elevated levels of the EIF4Ebp1 in TB mice, as EIF4Ebp1 levels have been found to correlate with cancer development and cachexia due to inhibition of protein synthesis via binding to eukaryotic initiation factor 4E (eIF4E).
